track-field-three-mountaineers-advance-to-ncaa-outdoor-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/track-field-three-mountaineers-advance-to-ncaa-outdoor-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000 meters at the NCAA East First Round" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team qualified three student-athletes for the NCAA Outdoor Championships following competition at the NCAA East First Round in Lexington, Kentucky.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg"><media:title>Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000 meters at the NCAA East First Round</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 23:01:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59150</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to Kentucky</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kentucky-2026</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kentucky-2026</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Gavin Kelly rounds the bases after hitting a home run against Kentucky." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team fell to Kentucky, 11-9, in the NCAA Regional winner's bracket game. The Mountaineers fall to 40-15 and will play Wake Forest in an elimination game on Sunday at 12 p.m. The Wildcats improve to 33-21 and advance to the regional final on Sunday at 5 p.m.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg"><media:title>Gavin Kelly rounds the bases after hitting a home run against Kentucky.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 21:41:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59149</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to Kentucky</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kentucky</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kentucky</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team fell to Kentucky, 11-9, in the NCAA Regional winner's bracket game. The Mountaineers fall to 40-15 and will play Wake Forest in an elimination game on Sunday at 12 p.m. The Wildcats improve to 33-21 and advance to the regional final on Sunday at 5 p.m.]]></description><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 21:41:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59148</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Defeat Binghamton to Open NCAA Regional</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/29/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-binghamton-to-open-ncaa-regional</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/29/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-binghamton-to-open-ncaa-regional</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Armani Guzman swings the bat against Binghamton in the NCAA Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/29/wvu_uk_regional-137.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va.  – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team opened NCAA Regionals with a 10-1 victory over Binghamton, Friday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 40-14 as they reached the 40-win plateau for the second straight season and third time in the last four seasons. The Bearcats fall to 31-21.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/29/wvu_uk_regional-137.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/29/wvu_uk_regional-137.jpeg"><media:title>Armani Guzman swings the bat against Binghamton in the NCAA Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/29/wvu_uk_regional-137.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 21:22:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59146</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Set to Open Morgantown Regional Against Binghamton</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/28/baseball-mountaineers-set-to-open-morgantown-regional-against-binghamton</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/28/baseball-mountaineers-set-to-open-morgantown-regional-against-binghamton</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Kendrick Family Ballpark is shown from above as the West Virginia baseball team prepares for NCAA Regionals" src="https: